ring whether the issue arises from controller class names generating duplicate operation IDs like \\\"ping\\\" in the same group. Separate groups should be fine, but what about same method names? Those seem okay. I realize I might need to disable the first app after a scan; the GreetingController is used, which springdoc recognizes for the endpoint. I think I'll need to edit annotations and maybe format the @Import in a multiline layout.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_snzMv68Lny80rHiJ82fdzu57|fc_08b12ebb63c17adf016a4023eb05d8819385fefcd432c524ad", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.springdoc/springdoc-openapi-starter-webmvc-ui/3.0.3/src/test/java/org_springdoc/springdoc_openapi_starter_webmvc_ui/Springdoc_openapi_starter_webmvc_uiTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    @SpringBootApplication(proxyBeanMethods = false)\n    @Import(GreetingController.class)\n    public static class TestApplication {", "newText": "    @SpringBootApplication(proxyBeanMethods = false,\n            scanBasePackages = \"org_springdoc.springdoc_openapi_starter_webmvc_ui.none\")\n    @Import(GreetingController.class)\n    public static class TestApplication {"}, {"oldText": "    @SpringBootApplication(proxyBeanMethods = false)\n    @Import({ PublicController.class, AdminController.class, GroupedOpenApiConfiguration.class })\n    public static class GroupedOpenApiApplication {", "newText": "    @SpringBootApplication(proxyBeanMethods = false,\n            scanBasePackages = \"org_springdoc.springdoc_openapi_starter_webmvc_ui.none\")\n    @Import({PublicController.class, AdminController.class, GroupedOpenApiConfiguration.class})\n    public static class GroupedOpenApiApplication {"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 447, "output": 2128, "cacheRead": 27136, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29711, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestam